# Oarmaker Yard — Illustration Prompt

Create a richly detailed, roughly square digital painting sized to sit beside narrative text on desktop or mobile screens. Depict a grounded late-medieval harbor campaign setting with long poles, hooks, shaved timber, collars, pegs, and workshop racks. Emphasize crisp readability, brighter maritime color accents, and clear spatial separation more than muddy painterly atmosphere.

- Composition: timber workshop yard with racks of poles and fittings, plus a visible route back to the town-harbor spine.
- Key elements: boat hooks, collar pins, wood shavings, benches, and half-finished practical gear.
- Character focus: makers whose work seems peripheral until the last blocker drags them into the war.
- Navigation hint: keep the return path toward Salt Storehouse visible and direct.

